{"title":"2022 Santa Cruz Bronson mixes wheel sizes for the best of both worlds","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/06/08/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mixes-wheel-sizes-for-the-best-of-both-worlds/","date":1623135667000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><p><span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-box-3\"></span>Santa Cruz and Juliana have updated their 150mm travel all-mountain bike, bringing a mullet platform into the mix. Like their Heckler and Bullit eMTBs, the 2022 Santa Cruz Bronson and Juliana Roubion run a 27.5″ wheel in the rear and a 29″ out front. Wanting to provide the very same ride feel to all riders, Santa Cruz have given each frame size-specific stays.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090853/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-yellow.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090853/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-yellow.jpg\" alt=\"2022 santa cruz bronson\" width=\"1200\" height=\"677\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090853/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-yellow.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090853/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-yellow-297x168.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090853/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-yellow-800x451.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090853/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-yellow-120x68.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090853/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-yellow-768x433.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090853/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-yellow-696x393.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090853/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-yellow-1068x603.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090853/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-yellow-744x420.jpg 744w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb13 src ng ngcb13 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090853/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-yellow.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090853/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-yellow.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090853/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-yellow-297x168.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090853/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-yellow-800x451.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090853/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-yellow-120x68.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090853/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-yellow-768x433.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090853/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-yellow-696x393.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090853/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-yellow-1068x603.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090853/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-yellow-744x420.jpg 744w\"></a></p><p>Santa Cruz are bang on trend with the 2022 Bronson, mixing up wheel sizes to give riders the best of both worlds. The XS is the only frame in the XS-XL size range to run a 27.5″ wheel front and back; the others get a mullet makeover. Another key update is the introduction of proportional length chainstays that get longer up the frame size range in line with a growing front-center. Let’s dive into the numbers.</p><ul><li>Bike: 2022 Santa Cruz Bronson</li><li>Frame: C and CC Carbon Layups</li><li>Wheel Size: 27.5″ rear, 29″ front</li><li>Fork Travel: 160mm</li><li>Rear Wheel Travel: 150mm</li><li>Claimed Frame &amp; Shock Weight: 3572g (Large CC w/ RS Super Deluxe Ultimate)</li><li>Starting Price: $5,049 USD</li></ul><figure id=\"attachment_261162\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-261162\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07091350/2022-juliana-roubion.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07091350/2022-juliana-roubion.jpg\" alt=\"2022 juliana roubion same frame as 2022 santa cruz bronson lighter shock tune\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07091350/2022-juliana-roubion.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07091350/2022-juliana-roubion-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07091350/2022-juliana-roubion-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07091350/2022-juliana-roubion-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07091350/2022-juliana-roubion-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07091350/2022-juliana-roubion-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07091350/2022-juliana-roubion-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07091350/2022-juliana-roubion-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb13 src ng ngcb13 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07091350/2022-juliana-roubion.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07091350/2022-juliana-roubion.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07091350/2022-juliana-roubion-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07091350/2022-juliana-roubion-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07091350/2022-juliana-roubion-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07091350/2022-juliana-roubion-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07091350/2022-juliana-roubion-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07091350/2022-juliana-roubion-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07091350/2022-juliana-roubion-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-261162\">The 2022 Juliana Roubion shares the same frame as the Santa Cruz Bronson, only with a lighter tune on the shock</figcaption></figure><p>For 2022, the Santa Cruz Bronson is both longer and slacker than its <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2018/07/03/santa-cruz-bronson-juliana-roubion-stretch-150mm-of-enduro-all-mountain-bike-from-trail-to-park/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">predecessor</a>. Across the XS-XL range, the head angle is just shy of 1° slacker (0.9°, to be exact), reach is on average 15mm longer, while the stack is 20mm taller. Reach now spans a 405mm to 500mm range, and chainstays <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/03/19/aasq-110-six-mountain-bike-frame-mfgs-discuss-proportional-length-chainstays/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">grow proportionally</a> with a range of 427mm to 442mm.<span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-medrectangle-3\"></span></p><figure id=\"attachment_261159\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-261159\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090755/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-vero-sandler.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090755/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-vero-sandler.jpg\" alt=\"2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090755/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-vero-sandler.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090755/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-vero-sandler-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090755/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-vero-sandler-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090755/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-vero-sandler-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090755/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-vero-sandler-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090755/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-vero-sandler-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090755/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-vero-sandler-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090755/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-vero-sandler-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb13 src ng ngcb13 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090755/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-vero-sandler.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090755/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-vero-sandler.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090755/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-vero-sandler-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090755/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-vero-sandler-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090755/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-vero-sandler-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090755/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-vero-sandler-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090755/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-vero-sandler-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090755/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-vero-sandler-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090755/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-vero-sandler-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-261159\">Despite Juliana’s lighter shock tune being marketed at female riders, freerider Veronique Sandler rides the Bronson</figcaption></figure><p>Santa Cruz are sticking with adjustable geometry, retaining a flip-chip at the lower shock mount. That said, the change is so infinitesimally small, we’re doubtful as to whether or not it will actually translate into a significantly different ride feel. Taking the large frame as an example; in the low setting, the BB sits at 341mm, the head angle at 64.5° and the seat tube angle at 76.5°, with a 472mm reach measurement between the two.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090651/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090651/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet.jpg\" alt=\"2022 santa cruz bronson\" width=\"1200\" height=\"703\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090651/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090651/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-297x174.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090651/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-800x469.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090651/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-120x70.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090651/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-768x450.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090651/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-696x408.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090651/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-1068x626.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090651/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-717x420.jpg 717w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb13 src ng ngcb13 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090651/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090651/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090651/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-297x174.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090651/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-800x469.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090651/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-120x70.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090651/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-768x450.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090651/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-696x408.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090651/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-1068x626.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090651/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-717x420.jpg 717w\"></a></p><p>Flipping the chip subtly adjusts those numbers to a 344mm bottom bracket height, a 64.7° HA and a 76.9° SA with a slightly increased reach of 475mm. Another small change is also seen the chainstays; switching from the low to the high geometry setting decreases the rear centre length by 1mm. The exception to that is seen on the XS frame where flipping the chip alters chainstay length by 5mm.&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com