s.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07093420/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-rear-end-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07093420/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-rear-end-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07093420/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-rear-end-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07093420/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-rear-end-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07093420/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-mullet-rear-end-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>The justification? “<em>The</em> [next generation VPP delivers a] <em>lower overall leverage while still offering progressive, linear rate. Lower leverage makes for a familiar, but more composed evolution of VPP. Lower instant center and anti-squat makes for less chain influence on the suspension: less pedal feedback</em>” – <strong>Santa Cruz Bicycles</strong>.</p><p><span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-box-4\"></span>Brand Manager Garen Becker tells us the Bronson has noticeably less pedal feedback than bike’s running the older version of the VPP Link, such as the Hightower and Tallboy. For an in-depth explanation of pedal feedback (or pedal kickback, as it is more commonly known), see Tyler’s video explainer <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/09/18/aasq-85-what-is-pedal-kick-back-full-suspension-chain-growth/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">here</a>.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090535/2022-Santa-Cruz-Bronson-geometry-mullet.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090535/2022-Santa-Cruz-Bronson-geometry-mullet.jpg\" alt=\"2022 juliana roubion geometry char