5mm-riser-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090940/2022-santa-cruz-carbon-handlebar-35mm-riser-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090940/2022-santa-cruz-carbon-handlebar-35mm-riser-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090940/2022-santa-cruz-carbon-handlebar-35mm-riser-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07090940/2022-santa-cruz-carbon-handlebar-35mm-riser-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-261161\">The new Santa Cruz Carbon Bar is available in a 35mm clamp option only</figcaption></figure><p>Santa Cruz have quietly slipped in a new carbon handlebar with the launch of the 2022 Bronson. They say the new layup makes the bar “easier on the hands”, or at least less abusive than the last one.<span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-leader-1\"></span></p><p>We can tell you that, while it comes stock on the five most expensive Bronson builds, it will actually be available aftermarket, too! It gets a 35mm rise, 8.5° backsweep and 5° upsweep, and comes 800mm wide. There’s a Di2 version, too.</p><h3>Pricing &amp; Availability</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07095432/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-factory-fox-suspension.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07095432/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-factory-fox-suspension.jpg\" alt=\"sc bronson 2022\" width=\"1200\" height=\"699\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07095432/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-factory-fox-suspension.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07095432/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-factory-fox-suspension-297x173.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07095432/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-factory-fox-suspension-800x466.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07095432/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-factory-fox-suspension-120x70.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07095432/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-factory-fox-suspension-768x447.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07095432/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-factory-fox-suspension-696x405.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07095432/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-factory-fox-suspension-1068x622.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07095432/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-factory-fox-suspension-721x420.jpg 721w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb13 src ng ngcb13 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07095432/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-factory-fox-suspension.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07095432/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-factory-fox-suspension.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07095432/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-factory-fox-suspension-297x173.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07095432/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-factory-fox-suspension-800x466.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07095432/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-factory-fox-suspension-120x70.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07095432/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-factory-fox-suspension-768x447.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07095432/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-factory-fox-suspension-696x405.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07095432/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-factory-fox-suspension-1068x622.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/07095432/2022-santa-cruz-bronson-factory-fox-suspension-721x420.jpg 721w\"></a></p><p>There are no fewer than seven models of the 2022 Santa Cruz Bronson, satisfying a range of budgets from $5,049, right up to an eye watering $11,399. The lower-end R, S, XT and XT RSV builds run a complete carbon frame, but it’s Santa Cruz’s “C” layup; slightly thicker and therefore heavier. The upper echelons get the “CC” layup; thinner, lighter (by around 200g on a large), but just as strong and stiff.</p><p>For complete information on the 2022 Santa Cruz Bronson model specifications and pricing, head to the Santa Cruz website.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.santacruzbicycles.com/en-GB\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>SantaCruzBicycles.com</em></a></p></div></div>","author":"Jessie-May Morgan","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"5f9d9fc518b54c10da11d8f431864fd6bd53b7b922508edb27688454e49023e4","category":"Cycling"}